Preliminary Visualisations of Parliamentary Networks

Nicholas Erskine

2018-11-22

As an illustration I reproduce figure 2 from (Andris 2015) using data from the Australian Senate. The authors consider the US house of representatives

library(Matrix)

adj_m <- adjacency_matrix_from_divisions(divisions,chamber_id = 'Senate',start_date = ymd('2018-01-01'))
sample(nrow(adj_m),10) %>% adj_m[.,.]  %>% graph_from_adjacency_matrix %>%
  ggraph() + 
  geom_edge_link(alpha=0.25) +
  geom_node_point(alpha=0.25)
## Using `nicely` as default layout

adj_m <- adj_m > 100
adj_m <- adj_m[colSums(adj_m) > 0,colSums(adj_m) > 0]
adj_m %>% 
    graph_from_adjacency_matrix(mode='undirected') %>%
    ggraph() +
    geom_edge_link(alpha=0.25) + 
    geom_node_point(alpha=0.25) + 
    theme_graph() + 
    geom_node_text(aes(label=name))
## Using `nicely` as default layout
